 1ab4ddca-d4f4-4d37-8ddf-6a838416ebdc.description=<pre>
 Usage instructions

This workflow is designed to patch Oracle Grid Infrastructure on 11.2 and 12.1 environments. The workflow will work for both Grid Standalone and Grid Cluster environments. The workflow is designed to run against the ASM Instance (+ASM, +ASM1) selected as the target and will handle patching any database homes and databases automatically though self discovery.

 Patching scenarios

 In-Place Patching

This option will patch GI, any database homes, and databases that have been included based on parameter inputs for the "Oracle Database Homes" parameter. Example parameters used for In-Place patching\:

|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|2 Phase Patching | False |
 |Clone Patching Database| False |
|Clone Patching Grid| False |
|Oracle Database Homes| ALL|
|RDBMS Homes Only| False |

 Clone Patching Single Phase

This option will clone grid and database home(s) that are specified to be patched. Once cloned the patch(s) will be applied to the cloned home. After patching is complete for grid and database homes switchover occurs to move grid services and database services to the newly patches homes. Example parameters user for Clone Patching Single Phase\:
|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|2 Phase Patching | False |
 |Clone Patching Database| True |
|Clone Patching Grid| True |
|Oracle Database Homes| ALL|
|RDBMS Homes Only| False |

 Clone Patching Two Phase

This option will clone grid and database home(s) that are specified to be patched. Once cloned the patch(s) will be applied to the cloned home. The workflow will then exit. The second phase is re-running the workflow at which point the workflow will identify the first phase of the workflow has been executed and will execute the switchover operations to move services to the new patched homes. Example parameters user for Clone Patching Two Phase\:
|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|2 Phase Patching | True |
 |Clone Patching Database| True |
|Clone Patching Grid| True |
|Oracle Database Homes| ALL|
|RDBMS Homes Only| False |

 Patch RDBMS Home(s) Only

This option can be used to patch database homes of a different version at a later date separate from patching Grid. This parameter can still be used with clone patching but will only effect the specified database home(s) part of the deployment. Example parameters user for Clone Patching Two Phase\:
|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|2 Phase Patching | False |
 |Clone Patching Database| True |
|Clone Patching Grid| True |
|Oracle Database Homes| ALL|
|RDBMS Homes Only| True |

 There are 4 options for patching Oracle Database Homes Parameter

 1) ALL - This option will patch every Oracle Database Home found on the selected target.
 2) NONE - This Option will only patch Grid and will leave all Database Homes as is.
 3) INCLUDE\:/u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/home_1,/u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/home_2 - This Option lets you specify only specific home(s) that should
 be patched with Grid
 4) EXCLUDE\:/u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/home_1,/u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/home_2 - This Option lets you specify only specific home(s) that should
be excluded while patching Grid


 One Off Patching

One Off patches can be applied using this workflow by specifying the one or many one off patches to be applied after the PSU. The parameter take a comma separated list of one off patch archive provide by Oracle. Example\:

|. *Parameter*|. *Value*|
|Oneoff Archives | p16836674_112040_Linux-x86-64.zip,p13571876_112046_Linux-x86-64.zip,p14059190_112040_Generic.zip |
